

>>> NOTE <<< 
In order to retreive the daemon from git, this need to be added to:
YOCTO/frdm-imx93/conf/local.conf

Append this line at the end:
IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " git"

Then bitbake the recipe from top YOCTO directory:
MACHINE=imx93frdm DISTRO=fsl-imx-xwayland source sources/meta-imx-frdm/tools/imx-frdm-setup.sh -b frdm-imx93
bitbake YOUR-RECIPE (e.g. imx-image-core)


>>> FOR REMOTE TESTING (via USB) use MINICOM  <<<
You may need to install (first try without): https://github.com/WCHSoftGroup/ch343ser_linux

sudo apt update
sudo apt install minicom
sudo usermod -aG dialout $USER  
 // use the above if you get permision errors
dmesg | tail
 // this will present the latest plugged USB; 
 // e.g. 
 // [13605.736401] usb_ch343 1-2:1.0: ttyCH343USB0: usb to uart device
 // [13605.736959] usb_ch343 1-2:1.0: USB to GPIO device now attached to ch343_iodev1
 // [13605.738415] usb_ch343 1-2:1.2: ttyCH343USB1: usb to uart device
sudo minicom -s
